# John Deere - Manufacturing Engineer Apprentice (Smart Connected Factory Analyst) 

## Core responsibilities and competencies required

- Develop a strong understanding of current business practices across various enterprises, particularly focusing on data management systems, SQL, and Python to support manufacturing processes.
- Present demos to supervisors and gather feedback, as well as deliver presentations to upper management stakeholders, ensuring clear communication of project progress and outcomes.
- Leverage detailed manufacturing process knowledge to understand how applications are utilized within the manufacturing environment, ensuring that technological solutions are effectively integrated and aligned with business needs.

## Essential technical skills

- Proficiency in SQL and Python for managing and analyzing data, supporting backend development, and creating robust solutions for the manufacturing environment.
- Experience in web application development to support the creation and integration of applications used in manufacturing processes.
- Strong knowledge of database management and data analysis/visualization to effectively handle large datasets and derive actionable insights that improve manufacturing processes.

## Additional skills and competencies

- Understanding of backend development and programming to create and maintain applications that enhance manufacturing operations.
- Experience with integration techniques to ensure seamless operation and communication between different systems and applications within the smart connected factory environment.
- Effective communication and presentation skills to clearly convey technical information to both technical and non-technical stakeholders, ensuring alignment and understanding across the organization.

## Courses

- [CS50's Introduction to Databases with SQL](https://pll.harvard.edu/course/cs50s-introduction-databases-sql) 
- [DataCamp](https://www.datacamp.com/) & [Join the Tea](https://www.datacamp.com/groups/shared_links/c465635668f58fe94b399c69dd1a68c9f92386d2e3616c35faac470e810e0fc5)
- [Dimitri Fontaine's The Art of PostgreSQL](https://theartofpostgresql.com/)
- [Python & Django](https://dpi.instructure.com/courses/301/assignments/2591)
- [Python for Everybody](https://online.umich.edu/series/python-for-everybody/)
- [Assignment CS50's Web Programming with Python and JavaScript](https://dpi.instructure.com/courses/301/assignments/3094)
